request.description:
This endpoint can be used to update the details of a sale already created. The endpoint is available for both admin and agent users.

This endpoint can currently be only used to edit sales of specific flow types and also sales that are not:

- cancelled

- sent

- anonymised

- locked

- Salesdock integration sales


The endpoint accepts mainly the following:

1. customer - This object contains all ther personal and address information of the customer.

2. product_questions - This object contains the product questions of the sale. A "delete" array passsed in this with product question identifiers, will remove existing product questions from the sale and an "upsert" array will insert/update product questions into the sale.

3. agreements - Agreemeent data need to be sent for orders. A "delete" array passsed in this with agreement idnetifiers, will remove existing agreements from the sale and an "upsert" array will insert/update agreements into the sale.

4. flow_default - This array will contain default flow specific information. Right now, it accepts one array called "products". These accept the add on products of the sale that can be modified. A sample json object os below


``` json
{
    "products": {
        "delete": {
            "section-identifier-1": [
                35,
                20
            ],
            "section-identifier-2": [
                1
            ]
        },
        "upsert": {
            "section-identifier-1": [
                {
                    "id": 431,
                    "quantity": "0"
                }
            ],
            "section-identifier-2": [
                {
                    "id": 792,
                    "quantity": "1"
                }
            ]
        }
    }
}

 ```

In the above request, the products in the delete array will be inserted and those in the upsert array will be updated or inserted. The identifier of the section needs to be also passed in these arrays (eg: section-identifier-1, section-identifier-2). Please also refer [https://developer.salesdock.nl/#a9de6f3c-dece-4942-9ade-06a8b3557abf](https://developer.salesdock.nl/#a9de6f3c-dece-4942-9ade-06a8b3557abf) for more information on how sales are inserted with multiple products.

This endpoint can be used to update the details of a sale that is finalized. So only accepted offers and direct orders can be updated with this API.

The confirmation PDF is not regenerated once a sale is updated via this endpoint.

This endpoint is only available for admin users. This endpoint can currently be only used to edit sales of specific flow types and also sales that are not:

- cancelled

- sent

- anonymised

- locked

